-- Taiwan Stocks: Everlight Electronics, Epistar, Largan Precision
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-04-13T05:56:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/taiwan-stocks-everlight-electronics-epistar-largan-precision.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 1.6 percent to 7,788.27, the
biggest jump since Feb. 29. The gauge advanced 1.1 percent this
week, the most in six weeks.  Light-emitting diode companies:  Epistar Corp. (2448)  (2448 TT)
surged 6.9 percent to NT$80.20, the biggest advance since Feb.
22.  Everlight Electronics Co. (2393)  (2393 TT) jumped 6.9 percent to
NT$65.50, the most since Feb. 21. The Ministry of Economic
Affairs said in a statement yesterday the government is planning
to replace current street lamps with LED models.  Largan Precision Co. (3008)  (3008 TT) advanced 2.7 percent to
NT$573, the highest close since March 30. The United Daily News
said Largan’s second-quarter revenue may rise as much as 15
percent, citing analyst estimates. Chief Financial Office Lin
En-Ping wasn’t immediately available for comment at his office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
